cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.RO

This paper deals with computer vision and machine learning techniques for generating and processing rainy images. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves training a de-raining model, which falls under the sub-category of machine learning, cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves generating diverse rainy images, which could be considered as a data augmentation technique, falling under the sub-category of artificial intelligence, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves robotics, as mentioned in the abstract, which could fall under the sub-category of graphics, cs.GR (Computer Graphics) or robotics, cs.RO (Robotics and Control).
